<TITLE> Youth trying to enter Dhaka jail arrested </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 13 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka Central Jail authorities Friday detained a youth from the jail gate when he tried to enter the compound passing for a BDR officer. The authorities turned named Abdur Rab Rabi, 25, in to police. They believed the youth is clinically insane. "It seems Rabi is mentally imbalanced. Police are interrogating him," deputy inspector general, prisons, Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui told bdnews24.com in the evening. Lalbagh Police Station duty-office sub-inspector Shafiqul Islam told bdnews24.com Rabi tried to enter the jail through the gate adjacent to Chawkbazar at about 5pm. When the jail guards stopped him Rabi identified himself as a BDR man and abused them. Later, on instruction from jail authorities, he was handed over to Lalbag police. Rabi told police he was the son of Haji Abul Hashem of Chowmuhoni in Begumganj, Noakhali. Jail guard Majed Hossain filed a case with Lalbag Police Station. bdnews
